    "client_msg_id": "12369573-234d-42ed-9a83-8df7d04be634",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "FWIW: A group of VC’s asked me to go and talk to Bret about Dynamicland. At that time they were running out of funds, and Bret was trying to figure out alternatives. My suggestion to him was threefold:\n1. Make a single person version of the rooftop (project plus camera) attachment and allow people to buy and use them on an individual basis.\n2. Take some of the killer use cases that were obvious (maps, and education) and drill deeper.\n3. Do not rely on the “benevolence model” of Carnegie funding the libraries equivalent, build up a customer base and determine your own destiny.\nThe problem is that there is a big difference between a demo and a product, and in many cases people want to build the former while others want to fund the latter.",
    "user": "U01JNTE35QS",
    "ts": "1667055858.986939",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "QPT",
        "elements": [
          {
